### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

forms

### Description

The signal forms doco on [Value transformation](https://angular.dev/guide/forms/signals/custom-controls#value-transformation) contains:

> ...and handle input events to parse user input back to the storage format

but any time user input is parsed there is the chance of invalid input, and hence errors, so I thought I would be able to add some validation there. But the very next section on Validation integration has a big warning:

> IMPORTANT: Don't implement validation logic in your control.

And there seems to be a fundamental gap there:

- The control may need to do validation to convert the user input into the model type.
- The schema validation can only run once the model type is pushed out via `value`.

Something as simple as the Currency input example in the docs:
```
handleInput(input: string) {
  const num = parseFloat(input.replace(/[^0-9.]/g, ''));
  if (!isNaN(num)) this.value.set(num);
}
```

- If the user types a valid number, that is passed up via the `value`.
- If they then continue typing making it an invalid number, the `value` is not changed and so the control remains valid even through they now have junk in the field.
- The only options the control has at this point are to clear the value or leave it at the last valid value - there is no way to report what the error is to the parent schema.

I would like to do this:
```
handleInput(input: string) {
  const num = parseFloat(input.replace(/[^0-9.]/g, ''));
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    const msg = `'${input}' is not a valid number.`;
    // pass msg back to framework validation
  } else {
    this.value.set(num);
  }
}
```

Changing the `FormUIControl.errors` to a model signal and allowing the control to pass errors back to its parent would seem to be one solution, although I can imagine there are many implementation details with the timing of when validation is run and what happens if both the schema and the control generate errors.

Here's a more complete example for a WidgetControl I am trying to convert from a `ControlValueAccessor` implementation: ([stackblitz](https://stackblitz.com/edit/stackblitz-starters-tk1jhcej?file=src%2Fwidget-input.ts)):

- A custom control that allows a user to type a code-number combination into a text box. The users know almost all of the ones they use and want to speed type them in.
- I had a similar thing working using `ControlValueAccessor`: the control taps in to the model-to-view and view-to-model chains and inserts a custom Validator as the first validator in the list.

### Proposed solution

Possibly make `FormUiControl.errors` a model signal, allowing the control to pass validation errors back to the framework?

### Alternatives considered

I tried to create a sub-form, but can't see how to get that to work. Ultimately I want the field to act like a any other field in the parent form:
```
<app-currency-input [field]="userForm.currency" />
```

